      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's easy to rationalize that way, but the truth is, you're not out of the woods yet. You've still got unfinished business to tend to, relationships to nurture, and experiences to gather. Resistance is validation, but it's also a form of stubbornness that can hold you back from truly letting go. It's not about finding peace in the end; it's about finding a sense of closure and moving forward, with the knowledge that you've lived a life with purpose, even if it's been fleeting.",
      "source": "target",
